        <bioghist id="ref35">
            <head>Historical Note</head>
            <p>In 1965, Time Inc. became interested in investing in foreign publishing companies. By October 1966, they had made their first deal and purchased 19% interest in Organizacion Editorial Novaro S.A., a leading Mexican magazine and book publisher. At that same time, Time-Life International executives, including Zachary Morfogen who would later become Books and Arts Associates’s managing director, were in Germany meeting with eight publishers in the hopes that they would be able to invest in one of the publishers. Ultimately Time Inc. invested in Rowohlt Taschenbuch Verlag purchasing one-third interest in the company. Two years after this purchase, Time Inc. purchased interest in Andre Deutsch Ltd, a British publishing house, and entered a joint venture with Salvat Editores S.A., a Spanish publisher, to distribute books and record directly by mail. With the growing number of foreign investments, Time Inc. needed to create a group to monitor their overseas investments. Out of this need, Books and Arts Associates was created. Along with overseeing these earlier investments, Books and Arts Associates also managed investments that Time Inc. made in Robert Laffont in France and Shingakusha-Time International in Japan as well as the 1978 joint venture Time Inc. entered with Little, Brown and Company in France and Japan that focused on publishing materials in the medical field. While Books and Arts Associates was listed as its own group within Time Inc. in Department Head Lists, and not as a subsidiary of the company, it was also a member of the Books Group along with Little, Brown and Company (Inc.), the Book-of-the-Month Club, Inc., and the New York Graphic Society Ltd.</p>
            <p>
                <emph render="underline">Works Cited:</emph></p>
            <p>Pendergast, Curtis and Geoffrey Colvin, 
                <title render="italic">The World of Time Inc.:The Intimate History of a Changing Enterprise 1960-1980 </title> (New York: Atheneum, 1986).</p>
            <p>Time Inc. 
                <title render="italic">1980 Annual Report</title>. 1981. http://www.thehistorycenteronline.com/collections/entry/category/annual-reports-time-inc.-temple-eastex, accessed June 2, 2017.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent id="ref36">
            <head>Scope and Contents Note</head>
            <p>The Books and Arts Associates Records cover the period of 1970 through 1981 and focus on the finances of Books and Arts Associates, a group within Time Inc. which monitored Time Inc.'s minority investments in foreign publishing houses. The majority of documents were created by or sent to Zachary Morfogen, the Managing Director of Books and Arts Associates. Included are newsletters, notes, strategic plans, budget reports, monthly and weekly operating reports, business objectives, account statements, invoices, international investment strategies, accounting policies and procedures, presentations on finances and income, and correspondences. The correspondence discusses social security benefits and payments, strategic plans, budgets, and operating reports.</p>
        </scopecontent>
